<P>
   OPEN-SOURCE (Undated) _ Software's ``open source'' effort, once
viewed as an ideological movement at the fringes of computing, is
moving into the mainstream _ largely because the spread of the
Internet and personal computers make it easy for programmers to
collaborate in far-flung, voluntary teams. But is there a viable
business model for open-source software? By Steve Lohr.
</P>
<P>
   PARACEL-CODEBREAK (Pasadena, Calif.) _ A behind-the-scenes look
at Paracel, whose supercomputers are used for breaking complex
codes _ whether the human genetic code, in the case of Celera
Genomics, or other sorts of code, in the case of the National
Security Agency. By Andrew Pollack.
