<P>
   STOCK-EXCHANGE-BID (London) _ OM Gruppen of Sweden, which owns
the Stockholm Stock Exchange, may make a $1.2 billion hostile
takeover bid for the London Stock Exchange. By Suzanne Kapner.
</P>
<P>
   WINDRIVER-ICESOFT (London) _ Wind River Systems, the maker of
software that is embedded in dozens of digital devices, will
announce Monday that it has agreed to acquire ICEsoft, a Norwegian
developer of Web browsing software for Internet appliances, for
$24.5 million in cash. By Andrew Ross Sorkin.
</P>
