   PATENTS (Undated) _ For generations, urban commuters have stood
on curbs in every kind of weather, doing the same dance: bodies
tilted, necks craned and eyes scanning the traffic horizon to see
if the bus is coming. Now there is an invention that could end
those contortions. The weekly patents column by Sabra Chartrand.
</P>
