   DEFIANT-PRAYER _ Determined not to be stopped by the U.S.
Supreme Court, students and grass-roots conservative groups across
the Bible Belt stood up last weekend and made a defiant statement:
They plan to pray at high school football games. The battle lines
were drawn, from the Carolinas across to Texas, with organized
efforts to challenge the Supreme Court's ruling in June prohibiting
student-led prayer at games and assemblies sanctioned by public
schools. Incidents were reported, with various levels of
participation, at scores of high school football games around the
South, and are likely to grow as word spreads. (Salzer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
