<SLUG> BC-RAC-SARATOGA-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PLEASANT BREEZE INJURED IN VICTORY 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. _ The front-running Pleasant Breeze
galloped to an easy gate-to-wire victory in the Saratoga Breeders'
Cup here Sunday but startled his trainer, James Bond, by pulling up
awkwardly after the finish line and being taken off in an equine
ambulance.
</P>
<P>
   A New York Racing Association veterinarian, Celeste Kunz, said
it did not appear as if the 5-year-old gelding had sustained a
fracture. ``He pulled up sore in his left front leg,'' she said.
``There does not appear to be any displacement of any bones, but he
is going back for evaluation. His leg was put in a splint.''
</P>
<P>
   His jockey, Jorge Chavez, said Pleasant Breeze ran smoothly
throughout the 1 1/4-mile race, in which he easily repelled the
challenge of the second- and third-place finishers, Catienus and
Gander.
</P>
<P>
   ``When we came back galloping nice and easy, I felt he was
missing a step,'' Chavez said. ``He seemed to be favoring his left
front. He could have stepped on a stone for all I know.''
</P>
<P>
   After X-rays were taken, Bond agreed that Pleasant Breeze's
injury appeared to be minor.
</P>
<P>
   ``We cannot find anything,'' the trainer said. ``We're hoping
it's just a wrench. He's 100 percent now. So far there's no heat or
swelling.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Pleasant Breeze won by 2 3/4 lengths in 2:02, paid $4.00 to win
and earned $180,000 for his owner, William L. Clifton Jr. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
