<SLUG> BC-WIRELESS-VENTURES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ECOMPANIES AND SPRINT PLAN WIRELESS VENTURE
</HEADLINE>
 By LAURA M. HOLSON    
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sprint's wireless division and the Internet incubator Ecompanies
plan to announce a new venture on Monday to finance start-up
companies in wireless communications.
</P>
<P>
   The venture, to be called Ecompanies Wireless, will receive a
$15 million investment from Spint's wireless unit, Sprint PCS, said
Bill Blessing, vice president for strategic planning at the
division.
</P>
<P>
   Like many wireless companies these days, Sprint PCS is eager to
capitalize on what industry executives hope will be exploding
demand for new types of data services and Internet access over
cellular phones and other wireless devices.
</P>
<P>
   Sprint PCS has announced several other forays in this area. Last
week it introduced its Wireless Web for Business, which will offer
wireless access to things like company e-mail and corporate
directories via Sprint PCS telephones. It also announced an
alliance with Wireless Knowledge, a company backed by Microsoft and
Qualcomm, which hopes to help business users receive company
services.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sprint is betting that they are moving so quickly they will be
the first to capitalize on any new technology,'' said Ira Brodsky,
president of Datacomm Research in St. Louis.
</P>
<P>
   Ecompanies, for its part, gets access to Sprint's expertise, as
well as its cash. Five Ecompanies executives are already working on
this project, said Sangam Pant, executive vice president at
Ecompanies. And a handful of Sprint PCS executives based in both
Santa Monica, Calif., home of Ecompanies, and Kansas City, Mo.,
where Sprint has its headquarters, will be on hand to advise
entrepreneurs. The new venture will be based in Santa Monica.
</P>
<P>
   The challenge will be to guess what services consumers really
want. Recently the stock prices of wireless concerns have
languished, in part because investors do not believe they have yet
delivered on the rosy growth predictions for wireless services.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-27-00 2105EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
