NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR MONDAY, AUG. 28 
</HEADLINE>
   (Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Monday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-COURT-TV-MEDIA-NYT (moved Sunday, August 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, August 19
about a planned Court TV series offering the videotaped confessions
of people accused of violent crimes misstated the outcome of a case
involving Daniel Rakowitz, who was taped confessing to the murder
and dismemberment of a woman in Manhattan in 1989. He was tried and
found not responsible by reason of insanity in 1991. He was not
judged unfit to stand trial.
</P>
